tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity), suggesting possible renal dysfunction. Mild hyperkalemia and hyperchloremia are present. Blood glucose and HbA1c are low, with glycosuria and ketonuria, raising concern for hypoglycemia and possible metabolic derangement. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend urgent clinical correlation for renal impairment and metabolic status.
